Sure! The code for the class `Solution` seen in the image is as follows:

```java
class Solution {
    public TreeNode mergeTrees(TreeNode t1, TreeNode t2) {
        if (t1 == null) {
            return t2;
        }
        if (t2 == null) {
            return t1;
        }

        t1.val += t2.val;
        t1.left = mergeTrees(t1.left, t2.left);
        t1.right = mergeTrees(t1.right, t2.right);
        return t1;
    }
}
```

This method merges two binary trees. If two nodes overlap, it sums node values and assigns them as the new value of the merged node. If one of the nodes is null, it returns the non-null node.
